        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 8:12PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 812 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Greensboro to near
Uniontown. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Greensboro, Newbern, Greensboro Municipal Airport, Vaiden,
Judson College, Morgan Springs, Vaiden Field Airport, Cedarville,
Laneville, and Folsom.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
